---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Nonprofit Disclosures | Jewmanity" description="Transparency about Jewmanity's 501(c)(3) status, use of funds, and organizational governance.">
  <section id="disclosures-hero" class="bg-primary-light py-20 pt-32 md:py-24 md:pt-36">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 text-center">
      <h1 class="font-heading text-[clamp(32px,5vw,48px)] font-medium leading-tight text-text-heading">
        Nonprofit Disclosures
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 font-heading text-lg text-text-muted">
        Transparency and accountability in everything we do
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="disclosures-content" class="py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="prose-legal mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6">
      <h2>Organization Information</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Legal Name:</strong> Jewmanity<br />
        <strong>Type:</strong> 501(c)(3) Nonprofit Organization<br />
        <strong>EIN:</strong> 99-4219099<br />
        <strong>Year Established:</strong> 2019<br />
        <strong>State of Incorporation:</strong> California
      </p>

      <h2>Tax-Deductible Status</h2>
      <p>
        Jewmanity is recognized by the Internal Revenue Service as a tax-exempt organization under Section 501(c)(3) of
        the Internal Revenue Code. All donations to Jewmanity are tax-deductible to the fullest extent allowed by law.
      </p>
      <p>
        Donors will receive a tax receipt via email for all contributions. For donations of $250 or more, a written
        acknowledgment will be provided as required by IRS regulations.
      </p>

      <h2>Mission Statement</h2>
      <p>
        Jewmanity is dedicated to supporting mental health and healing for Jewish and Israeli communities through
        rehabilitation retreats, peer support programs, education, and ongoing care resources.
      </p>

      <h2>Use of Funds</h2>
      <p>
        Jewmanity is committed to responsible stewardship of all contributions. Our programs include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Heads Up Healing Retreats</strong> — Comprehensive rehabilitation retreats in San Diego for Israeli
          soldiers, widows, widowers, and family members experiencing PTSD and trauma
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Community &amp; Peer Support</strong> — Group sessions and peer networks that foster understanding and
          mutual support
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Education &amp; Awareness</strong> — Workshops and resources addressing mental health stigma, trauma,
          and antisemitism
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Ongoing Care Resources</strong> — Therapist referrals, mental health tools, and continuing support
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Financial Transparency</h2>
      <p>
        We believe in complete transparency about how donations are used. The average cost to support one participant
        through a healing retreat is approximately $4,500, which covers:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>International flights: $1,200</li>
        <li>Housing and accommodations: $800</li>
        <li>Therapy and clinical support: $1,500</li>
        <li>Meals and nutrition: $400</li>
        <li>Program activities and logistics: $600</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Administrative costs are kept minimal to ensure maximum impact from every contribution.</p>

      <h2>Board of Directors</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Belinda Donner, Founding Board Member</li>
        <li>Andrew Donner, Founding Board Member</li>
        <li>Shai Gino, Executive Director</li>
        <li>Rabbi Avi Libman, Board Member</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about our nonprofit status, financial practices, or organizational governance, please contact us
        at <a href="mailto:info@jewmanity.org">info@jewmanity.org</a> or through our
        <a href="/get-involved/contact">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose-legal h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 24px;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-top: 48px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .prose-legal h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .prose-legal p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 28px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .prose-legal ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .prose-legal ul li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 24px;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 28px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .prose-legal ul li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 10px;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .prose-legal strong {
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .prose-legal a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: text-decoration 0.2s;
  }

  .prose-legal a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
